# Clean Architecture — layer mapping (this workspace)

## Absolutes

- **Allowed import edges** are defined only by `@nx/enforce-module-boundaries` → `depConstraints` in `eslint.config.mjs`. Do not rely on this file to invent new allowed edges; use it to **name** rings and **reason** about direction.
- **Before any new cross-library import**, confirm the source and target libraries’ `nx.tags` satisfy `depConstraints`.

## Ring → primary `scope:*` tags

- **Entities / enterprise rules:** `scope:contract`, `scope:protocol`, `scope:prompts`, `scope:shared`, `scope:async`, `scope:colors`, `scope:strings`
- **Use cases / application:** `scope:runtime`, `scope:session`
- **Interface adapters:** `scope:core`, `scope:adapters`, `scope:vercel-ai-sdk-adapter`
- **Frameworks & drivers:** `scope:react`, `scope:angular`, `scope:ai-connect`, `scope:ai-engine`, `scope:starter-kit`, `scope:starter-kit-ai`, `scope:playground`, `scope:demo`

## Dependency direction (conceptual)

```mermaid
flowchart TB
  drivers[drivers_apps_frameworks_vendors]
  adapters[adapters_facades_sdk_wrappers]
  application[application_runtime_session]
  domain[domain_contract_protocol]

  drivers --> adapters
  drivers --> application
  drivers --> domain
  adapters --> application
  adapters --> domain
  application --> domain
```

## Enforcement follow-ups (separate from rule text)

- Keep **documented policy** and **`depConstraints`** aligned. If a package is tagged and depended on but not named in `depConstraints`, treat that as a **tooling gap to fix in a dedicated change** (for example `scope:protocol` is used by `packages/runtime` but is not listed in `depConstraints` today).

## Defaults

- Prefer **adding** or **adjusting** `depConstraints` and tags in the same change when you intentionally introduce a new architectural edge, so agents and CI stay consistent.
